The paper deals with the problem of polynomial identity testing for noncommutative arithmetic circuits, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory. The techniques used in the paper involve structural results for noncommutative circuits, which are closely related to circuit complexity and algebraic complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper also involves some techniques from algebraic geometry and linear algebra, which could potentially place it in the sub-categories cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
